      "content": "that's a really solid start. it definitely hits the \"injustice\" angle well. can you expand on the part about meritocracy though? like, some people argue that wealth is just a result of hard work/talent and redistributing it is actually unfair to those who earned it. how can i frame that counter-argument in my paper so it looks weak or logically flawed compared to the redistribution argument? i want to make sure the reader sees it as an outdated or incorrect way of looking at things.",
